Plenty of air for us to share.
Take a walk and laugh my dear.
Skip along the fat sidewalk
Glance in a window and hum a tune.
Watch the night sky to see a bat fly by.


Make up a word like meesh.
Dance with me hand in hand.
Walk along a pumpkin patch.
Pick a flower, a daisy or two.
Hey watch me, with the words i match.

Some technique you made up.
Mixed a word with a rhyme for you.
Don't take  advantage of the time.
Take a moment to smell the flowers.
Erase your problem, fight or dilemma

Fingers locked with hope in sight.
You're one of a kind, she said with passion.
Acquantinces near and far.
The world sees you from a different place.
You judge the ones you may love.
Regret it once you think of it.

Take a walk with hope.
Maybe just hold on for a little bit.
Slip your slender hand into a little black glove.
The leaves may cover, but take a seat in a park on a bench.
Throw the bread at a dove or two.
Strangers walk by, but don't fret.

You may meet someone old someone new.
Take it from a word you've heard before.
Because if you're willing to bet..
You may find a clue.
No matter how many people you ignore, you never know what's instore.
You may just find someone to adore.

I lost my grace.
Where to go when nothing's happening.
We glance across to see nothing but a reflection in the puddle.
If it's what you want, then that's what it will be.
I'd really rather not meddle in what's not my dream.
I locked the door, and lost the key.
Now no one knows who or what it will be.
Although we're nothing what we seem.
Skip by my side in the downpour of rain.
The water up to our knees.
Skip and sing Merririririrlly.
One word lost in your travels.
I saw through the book.
You skipped the drama, and found your grace.

Think of yourself when you get the courage.
Remind the past of your regrets.
Rewind the tapes of the words you once recorded.
I see you in a light, a light like no other.
You already know how you see me through your eyes.
We decided long ago.
But it was just yesterday it seems.
Forget me not from what i act upon.
Recall my memories with me one day.
Figure out our regrets someday.
Still we sit, and wait, and hold on.

Locked fingers.
Side by side.
One day followed by the many more to come.
The day we wait for.
Is slowly coming.

One thing i want to hold on to.
Many things i've told you.
One whisper.
Some love spit.
A dance.
Some pictures.
And my love.
My heart, my mind, my love, my spirit, my grace (not much of that)


One song, and the moment's over.
Call me crazy, you know it's me.
I see your beauty throughout your actions.
I want you to know.
You could be a serial killer.
and i'd still bake you cookies.
and love you the same.

Hold the door, i'm coming too.

She was the girl i never knew.
One more moment, until the event.





Flowers of memories
Wisdom of lies.
The youngest one runs to you, with watery eyes.

Hold the flower until it wilts.
Erase the lies and all the guilt.
Hold the tears back with all your might.

By now you should know it gets dark at night.
Dreams of hope, and fears of life.
Extrordinary messages seen throughout the time.

The time flew by, with the words.
The world you saw through your eyes, never returned.
Amazing thoughts you finally learned.

Hand the flower back to the earth.
Wrap up tight in a bundle of truth.
Dry those teary eyes, and find your way.
